DESCRIPTION:Tickets $45\nPurchase Tickets\nAn enchanting celebration of strings featuring Palestinian oud/violin maestro\, and critically acclaimed Iranian kamancheh virtuoso and vocalist.\n\nFor this extraordinary concert celebrating World Music Institute’s 40th Anniversary—presented by in partnership with Roulette—we are thrilled to showcase two generations of master musicians who exemplify remarkable talent: Palestinian oud and violin maestro and educator\nSimon Shaheen\n\, who is is recognized as one of the most prominent Arab musicians of our time\, celebrated for his exceptional abilities in both traditional and contemporary music\; and\nMehrnam Rastegari\n\, a critically acclaimed Iranian kamancheh virtuoso\, vocalist\, and award-winning film composer who has graced prestigious stages around the globe.\nThis evening promises to be an enchanting celebration of strings.\nWorld Music Institute’s\n40TH ANNIVERSARY LEGACY\nseries features artists who have played an integral role in the 40-year history of the organization\, have been frequently presented by WMI throughout the years\, and have significantly contributed to the organization’s standing in New York’s cultural landscape.\nMore information at World Music Institute\nhere\n.\nPresented by WMI in partnership with Roulette. Roulette Membership benefits do not apply.
DURATION:PT2H
LOCATION:Roulette Intermedium\, 509 Atlantic Ave\, Brooklyn\, NY
DTSTART:20260522T000000Z
SUMMARY:Simon Shaheen with Mehrnam Rastegari (WMI)
UID:6c985faa-e581-40a4-843d-b3dd317f9149@6c98.org
